      <div xml:id="pl-l4d3c3">
        <head xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-Hd1e109">CAP. III</head>
        <p xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-d1e112">
          Legitur tamen in 
          <ref xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-Rd1e116" corresp="#pl-l4d3c3-Qd1e122"><title>Actibus Apostolorum</title></ref>, 
          Apostolos baptizasse 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-Qd1e122" ana="#act8_12">in nomine Christi</quote>
            <bibl>Actus 8:12</bibl>
          </cit>; 
          sed in hoc nomine, ut exponit 
          <ref xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-Rd1e129" corresp="#pl-l4d3c3-Qd1e114"><name>Ambrosius</name></ref>, 
          tota Trinitas
          intelligitur: 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-Qd1e114">
              Intelligitur enim, cum Christum dicis, et
              Pater, a quo unctus est, et ipse qui unctus est, et Spiritus sanctus, per quem unctus
              est
            </quote>
            <bibl>Ambrosius, De spiritu sancto, I, c. 3., n. 44 (PL 16:745)</bibl>
          </cit>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-d1e118">
          Unde <ref xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-Rd1e142" corresp="#pl-l4d3c3-Qd1e120"><name>Nicolaus papa</name></ref> : 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-Qd1e120" source="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p3d4-d1e470">
              A quodam Iudaeo multos baptizatos asseritis, 
              et quid inde agendum sit, 
              consulitis. 
              Hi profecto, 
              si in nomine sanctae Trinitatis, 
              vel 
              <quote xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-Qd1e150" ana="#act8_12">in nomine Christi</quote>, 
              sicut in 
              <ref xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-Rd1e153" corresp="#pl-l4d3c3-Qd1e150"><title>Actibus Apostolorum</title></ref> 
              legimus, 
              baptizentur, 
              baptizati sunt;
              unum enim idemque est, 
              ut 
              <ref xml:id="pl-l4d3c3-Rd1e157">
                sanctus exponit <name ref="#Ambrose">Ambrosius</name>
              </ref> 
            </quote>
          </cit>.
        </p>
      </div>
